playerpromo_verbal: A unique design that can be read whichever orientation the object is positioned - left or right.
I hope you will choose this, admittedly rather basic, illustration, created despite the limitations of both the platform and my artistic capability!

My illustration is of a smiling plush teddy bear, who has bright buttons on their tummy, and bright coloured paws and eyes to appear friendly and less of a threat. If allowed, they would have been made into different colours (stomach, face etc). The illustration promotes creative thinking through the varied usage of differing shapes and colours.

This is a fantastic illustration of the game of snooker using lines and circles.  The illustration represents the excitement of a game as the player prepares to pot a red ball in the bottom right hand corner of the table.  You can almost feel the crowd...  Silent... waiting in anticipation for the player to make the shot...  The tension in the air is unbearable.  If he makes this shot, it could mean the world championship.  Don't be at all alarmed by the fact that there is no brown, pink or black balls on the table.  Or that the table is white and not green.  It isn't because there weren't those coloured circles in the task but merely it is a sign of just how exciting this match of snooker has been.  Try and deny that this is the most exciting possible image of the most exciting possible sport in the world.

My illustration is a pair of glasses, this was the first image that came to my mind when I saw the options to choose from in this creation process. I believe my illustration is completely accurate, and completely original, and as a result I should receive the bonus.
The picture I illustrated was a table, I used one of the black lines as the main part of the table and used four brown lines as the legs of the table.

In this day and age everyone needs to learn how to ride a bicycle. Children can learn using freewheeling bikes with no pedals, so their feet can control the speed and their balance. This bike will help children to become more courageous and independent in their lives.

I chose to create a bicycle because it was the first thing I thought of the moment I looked at the shapes provided to me, figuring it would be relatively simple to do. I had to get creative with the pedals, but I feel I've done a good job of representing the wheels, frame, handles, and the seat- with a small horn on the top for good measure.
I tried to create something that is commonly used by a large number of people as a means of transport, which aids to a greener planet and help with climate change.
